  <content>
    <procedure>
      <preliminaryRqmts>
        <reqCondGroup>
          <reqCond id="RC001_TEST">
            <para>Ensure aircraft electrical power is available and stable (APU or Ground Power). Refer to AMM Chapter 24.</para>
          </reqCond>
          <reqCond id="RC002_TEST">
            <para>Verify Ramp Test Set, Model [MODEL_XYZ], is available and has valid calibration (within last 12 months).</para>
          </reqCond>
          <reqCond id="RC003_TEST">
            <para>Obtain clearance from airport authorities for use of test frequencies if required.</para>
          </reqCond>
        </reqCondGroup>
        <reqSafety>
          <safetyPrecautionGroup>
            <warning id="WARN_RF_RADIATION">
              <para>RF RADIATION HAZARD. During transmit tests, ensure all personnel are clear of the VHF antenna radiation keep-out zones as specified in AMM 20-00-01. Post warning placards.</para>
              <figureRef internalRefId="FIG_ANTENNA_KOZ"/>
            </warning>
            <caution id="CAUT_EQUIP_DAMAGE_POWER">
              <para>Ensure correct test equipment connections before applying power to prevent damage to aircraft systems or test set.</para>
            </caution>
          </safetyPrecautionGroup>
        </reqSafety>
        <reqSupportEquips>
          <supportEquipDescrGroup>
            <supportEquipDescr id="TE001_RAMP_TEST_SET">
              <name>Ramp Test Set, VHF Communications</name>
              <descr>Used for transmit/receive checks and signal quality measurements.</descr>
              <partOrConfigNumber>[MODEL_XYZ]</partOrConfigNumber>
              <manufacturerCodeValue>[CAGE_CODE_TEST_SET_MFR]</manufacturerCodeValue>
              <quantity>1</quantity>
            </supportEquipDescr>
          </supportEquipDescrGroup>
        </reqSupportEquips>
        <reqSpares><noSpares/></reqSpares>
        <reqSupplies><noSupplies/></reqSupplies>
        <refs>
          <dmRef id="REF_AMM_CH24">
            <dmIdent><dmCode modelIdentCode="B777" systemDiffCode="A" systemCode="24" infoCode="000"/></dmIdent>
            <dmAddressItems><dmTitle><techName>Electrical Power</techName><infoName>General</infoName></dmTitle></dmAddressItems>
          </dmRef>
          <externalPubRef id="REF_TEST_SET_MANUAL">
            <externalPubCode>[TEST_SET_MANUAL_ID]</externalPubCode>
            <externalPubTitle>Ramp Test Set [MODEL_XYZ] User Manual</externalPubTitle>
          </externalPubRef>
          <externalPubRef id="REF_ARINC716">
            <externalPubCode>ARINC 716</externalPubCode>
            <externalPubTitle>Airborne VHF Communications Transceiver</externalPubTitle>
          </externalPubRef>
        </refs>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <title>VHF Transceiver No.1 Functional Test</title>
        <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP001">
          <title>System Power-Up and BITE Check</title>
          <para>On the flight deck, ensure VHF COMM 1 power switch on the [Audio Control Panel / Overhead Panel - specify] is ON. Refer to <figureRef internalRefId="FIG_VHF_CTRL_PNL"/>.</para>
          <para>Observe the VHF Control Panel for normal power-on indications.</para>
          <para>Initiate the VHF Transceiver No.1 BITE test as follows:</para>
          <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP001_SUB1">
            <para>[Specific BITE initiation steps, e.g., Press and hold TEST button for 3 seconds].</para>
          </proceduralStep>
          <para>Observe BITE results displayed. A successful test is indicated by [Specify indication, e.g., "VHF1 OK" message or green status light]. Refer to <figureRef internalRefId="FIG_BITE_DISPLAY_EX"/>.</para>
          <para>If BITE indicates a fault, record fault code and refer to Fault Isolation DM <dmRef><dmIdent><dmCode modelIdentCode="B777" systemDiffCode="A" systemCode="23" subSystemCode="12" subSubSystemCode="11" infoCode="500"/></dmIdent></dmRef>.</para>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP002">
          <title>Transmit/Receive Check with Ramp Test Set</title>
          <para>Connect the Ramp Test Set <toolRef internalRefId="TE001_RAMP_TEST_SET"/> to the aircraft's No.1 VHF antenna test port. Refer to <figureRef internalRefId="FIG_RAMP_TEST_CONNECT"/> and <externalPubRef internalRefId="REF_TEST_SET_MANUAL"/>.</para>
          <warning internalRefId="WARN_RF_RADIATION"/> <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP002_SUB1">
            <para>On the VHF Control Panel, select test frequency [e.g., 121.5 MHz].</para>
            <para>Using the Ramp Test Set, initiate a transmission from the aircraft on the selected frequency. Verify power output is within [X dBm +/- Y dB] tolerance.</para>
          </proceduralStep>
          <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP002_SUB2">
            <para>Using the Ramp Test Set, transmit a test signal to the aircraft on the selected frequency.</para>
            <para>On the flight deck audio panel, monitor received audio from VHF 1. Verify audio is clear and intelligible. Verify signal strength indication (if available) is normal.</para>
          </proceduralStep>
        </proceduralStep>

        <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP003">
          <title>ATC Communication Check (Optional and Coordinated)</title>
          <note><para>This step is to be performed only if authorized and coordinated with local airport/ATC authorities.</para></note>
          <para>Select an appropriate ground control or clearance delivery frequency on VHF 1.</para>
          <para>Attempt a brief communication with ATC. Verify clear two-way communication.</para>
        </proceduralStep>
        
        <proceduralStep id="TEST_STEP004">
          <title>Record Results</title>
          <para>Record all test steps performed and their results (Pass/Fail, observed values) in the Aircraft Logbook.</para>
        </proceduralStep>
      </mainProcedure>
      
      <closeUpRqmts>
        <reqCondGroup>
          <reqCond id="RC_CU001_TEST">
            <para>Disconnect Ramp Test Set <toolRef internalRefId="TE001_RAMP_TEST_SET"/>.</para>
          </reqCond>
          <reqCond id="RC_CU002_TEST">
            <para>Return VHF Communication system and aircraft electrical power to normal configuration. Remove any warning placards.</para>
          </reqCond>
        </reqCondGroup>
      </closeUpRqmts>
    </procedure>
